@canisLupus1313  The `WaitResponse ` is waiting for the response from [ncp_base.cpp#L857](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/main/src/ncp/ncp_base.cpp#L857), rather than [ncp_base.cpp#L1212](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/main/src/ncp/ncp_base.cpp#L1212). After the RCP is restarted, it sends out the RESET reason to the host automatically.

I think the root cause of your issue is that: After the RCP is restarted, it sends out the RESET reason to the host. However, the host is  [re-opening](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/main/src/posix/platform/hdlc_interface.cpp#L724) the UART. Then the RESET reason from the RCP is lost. In the [original code](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/pull/8858/files#diff-f499bfcd3d5488045b07a03a07615ffa319ae7af6f193cf0e237674c4f407a8eR1741), the  `WaitResponse` always return `OT_ERROR_NONE `. There is no problem so far. But the [PR9278](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/pull/9278) changes the return error code, which causes your issue. So the key is that the RESET reason is lost.

The [kOpenFileDelay](https://github.com/openthread/openthread/blob/main/src/posix/platform/hdlc_interface.hpp#L238) is set to 500ms by default. It means the host has to wait `500ms` when failed to open the UART. During the waitting time, the RESET reason may be missed. You can try to set the `kOpenFileDelay` to 1 to check if the host will miss the RESET reason.

