similar feedback I make occasionally: recommend `return`ing early rather than "falling through" the conditionals and checking result at the end. For example:

```javascript
function callback(newValue) {
  const prop = [...subPaths, propertyName];
  const mod = moduleName ? moduleName : 'root';
  if (subSchema.type) {
    if (subSchema.type === Object && !isPlainObject(newValue)) {
      logging.error(
        `Validation failed for property: ${property} in module ${mod}: ${newValue} should be Object`
      );
      return;
    } else if (!(newValue instanceof subSchema.type)) {
      logging.error(
        `Validation failed for property: ${property} in module ${mod}: ${newValue} should be ${subSchema.type}`
      );
      return;
    }
  }
  if (subSchema.validator && !subSchema.validator(newValue)) {
    logging.error(
      `Validation failed for property: ${property} in module ${mod}: ${newValue} failed validation.`
    );
  }
}
```

