@RehanSD I agree that if we want to get the samples and the axis=1 full-axis partitions with a single remote call, (4) is the best solution. However, I'm still uncomfortable with (4) because getting two results out of a single call seems like a very particular use case of `apply_full_axis` that no one else will want. Really what you are doing here is pipelining two remote steps and also getting the result of each. The first step is effectively making full-axis-1 virtual partitions and `force_materialization()`ing them, and the other is applying a sampling function to each axis partition.

Is it possible to use the batch API to pipeline the two functions and only materialize the results of the sampling, then use the axis partition results from the first step? Otherwise, can you think of some other clean way to combine the functions and get the sample out with a single remote get?

In the absence of a cleaner solution, I can accept solution (4) for its performance benefit, but you should add a note explaining why we are doing this.

